{
  "stem": "26142.9",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were in Dolina and, as I mentioned, in Dolina we knew that we had some family there from our mother's side, the Drimmers.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This family that Moshe stayed at, their son took us over to show us where the family, Drimmer, lives.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We came in, only Tsvi and I came in there, and we introduced ourselves.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we said, we are Drimmers from-- they knew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They knew that they had family, that they had family in former Czechoslovakia, and they were very nice to us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We could feel right away that this is more than just-- we felt that we are among family.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And this family, they had a beautiful pair of teenage boys, twins.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were about 14 or 15 years of age at that time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the reason why I'm mentioning that, because it was very unusual, they were growing gray hair.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were very nice kids.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they told me, we only have room for one person.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But they had in-laws that lived across the street from them that one of us can go over to-- they will take care of one of us.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it turned out that my older brother, Tsvi stayed with them, and I was the one to go over to their in-laws.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were not relatives.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] in that house was a young girl, maybe a year younger than I was, and it turned out that she belonged to the same Betar organization, Zionist organization, that I belonged in Czechoslovakia before.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we felt a fraternal-- how should I say that-- closeness.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she was a secretary at the Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She worked in the Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Judenrat had made kitchens that they would cook for refugees, Hungarian refugees, that filtered back in there.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
